# ðŸš€ Soneium Node Setup Guide

This repository contains a simple BASH script for quickly setting up, building, and running a full node for the **Soneium Chain**.

## Prerequisites

* Linux operating system (Ubuntu 20.04/22.04 recommended)
* Go (version 1.21+) installed
* Git and essential build tools (`make`, `gcc`)

## Installation Script (Quick Start)

Copy and paste the entire block below into your terminal. This script will install all necessary packages, clone the Soneium repository, build the binary, initialize the node, and start the service.

```bash
#!/bin/bash

# --- SONEIUM NODE SETUP SCRIPT ---

# 1. Update system and install dependencies
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install curl git make gcc snapd -y

# 2. Install Go (if not installed or if version is too old)
if ! command -v go &> /dev/null || [[ "$(go version | grep -oP 'go\d+\.\d+' | cut -d'.' -f2)" -lt 21 ]]; then
    echo "Installing or updating Go..."
    # Install Go 1.21+
    wget -q -O - [https://raw.githubusercontent.com/canha/golang-tools-install-script/master/goinstall.sh](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/canha/golang-tools-install-script/master/goinstall.sh) | bash -s -- --version 1.21.5
    export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin:$HOME/go/bin
fi

# 3. Clone the official repository (Replace with actual Soneium repo if different)
# Using placeholder command based on standard Cosmos convention:
echo "Cloning Soneium repository..."
git clone [https://github.com/Soneium/Soneium-chain.git](https://github.com/Soneium/Soneium-chain.git)
cd Soneium-chain

# 4. Build the binary (Replace 'soneiumd' with the actual binary name if needed)
echo "Building Soneium binary..."
make install

# Check if build was successful
if ! command -v soneiumd &> /dev/null; then
    echo "ERROR: soneiumd binary build failed. Check Go installation."
    exit 1
fi

# 5. Initialization
NODE_MONIKER="My_Soneium_Validator"
CHAIN_ID="soneium-testnet-1" # (Use the actual chain-id)

# Initialize the node
soneiumd init $NODE_MONIKER --chain-id $CHAIN_ID

# Download the genesis file (Placeholder URL - REPLACE with actual URL from Soneium portal)
curl -s [https://soneium.org/genesis.json](https://soneium.org/genesis.json) > $HOME/.soneiumd/config/genesis.json

# 6. Add persistent peers (Crucial for testnets - REPLACE with actual list)
PERSISTENT_PEERS="peer_id_1@ip_1:port_1,peer_id_2@ip_2:port_2"
sed -i.bak -e "s/^persistent_peers *=.*/persistent_peers = \"$PERSISTENT_PEERS\"/" $HOME/.soneiumd/config/config.toml

echo "Setup complete. Binary built and node initialized. Run 'soneiumd start' to sync."
